Get ready to start the game!

Thank you for reading the instructions. Get ready start with the 40 rounds of this game.

If you need to take a break, feel free to take one after the end of a round, before continuing to the next one.

Remember, the more money the spider gets, the bigger your bonus will be!

Press space to begin.


(If, at any point, the space key does not take you to the next page, click once on the text and try again.)

response.Q0: To click on each of the first three directions the spider could move in, to see which one had a negative score.  But after four or five games I changed my tactic to click on the outer (5th) choices, to find one with a good score.
response.Q1:
I would click to try and find a high ($70-80) score, sacrificing 3-6 clicks in doing so. If I found a $40-60 score, then I would make one extra click, to see if I could get a higher score, if not, then I would settle.
The more minus ($-) that I found, then the more I would click to try and find a positive score.
response.Q2: I could have sacrificed more clicks, once I found a good score ($70-80) I would not check the route to it, there could have been a lot of negative score to pick up on the way, that would have made settling for a lower score, with more positive bonuses on the way even more profitable.  But I did not want to spend too much on clicking every possible route, so I would just settle for the end score, and pick up any negatives along the way without knowing until the end.

I was not paying particular attention to the cost of clicking on the markers, for the first 2-3 games I did not even notice the cost as I was just getting used to the game, then for the next few I looked to see if the price varied, and would apply more or fewer clicks if this happened.  Whenever I looked at the price it always seemed set at the same price, but I was looking more at the revealed tokens to focus solely on the charge for every click.  I thought that the price would vary, and maybe it did, but I only saw one price whenever I tried to check quickly between clicks.
